  "title": "How to use if in html",
  "description": "This will show you how to use the if condition in html while in Angular",
  "text": "Some times you want to have a condition if it should do something or not and for that angular has the *ngIf\nHere is a simple example for how to use it",
  "content": [
    {
      "data": 2,
      "text": "//Ts file\nimport { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';\n\n@Component({\n  selector: 'app-how-to-if',\n  templateUrl: './how-to-if.component.html',\n  styleUrls: ['./how-to-if.component.css'],\n})\nexport class HowToIfComponent implements OnInit {\n  showTitle: boolean = true;\n  showText: boolean = true;\n  constructor() {}\n\n  ngOnInit(): void {}\n\n  checkIfShowText(): boolean {\n    //Do some other Checks if it should be true or not\n    return this.showText;\n  }\n}\n"
    },
    {
      "data": 2,
      "text": "//Html \n<div>\n  <p *ngIf=\"showTitle\">My title or any other content</p>\n  <button *ngIf=\"checkIfShowText()\">Press it!</button>\n</div>\n"
    },
    {
